olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 stalk celery
1 carrot
1 leek
1 packet gnocchi
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet Red Wine Jus
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
½ tbs brown sugar
20 g butter
2 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet parsley

• Finely chop garlic, celery and carrot. Thinly slice leek.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook gnocchi, tossing occasionally, until golden, 6-8 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

TIP: Add extra oil if the gnocchi sticks to the pan.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add pork mince, breaking up with a spoon and cook, until just browned, 3-5 minutes.
• Add celery, leek and carrot, then cook until tender, 4-6 minutes.

• Add Aussie spice blend, tomato paste and garlic and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Reduce heat to medium-low, then add red wine jus, chicken-style stock powder, the brown sugar, butter and a splash of water. Simmer,
until slightly reduced, 3-4 minutes.

• Return gnocchi to the pan and stir to combine.

• Divide pork and red wine ragu gnocchi between bowls.
• Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!